Interface Positionable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApplicationDescriptor, ApplicationSnapshotDescriptor, CoreDumpDescriptor, CoreDumpsContainerDescriptor, DataSourceDescriptor, DataSourceView, DefaultCustomizer, HeapDumpDescriptor, JmxConnectionCustomizer, LocalHostDescriptor, PropertiesProvider, RemoteHostDescriptor, RemoteHostsContainerDescriptor, SnapshotCategory, SnapshotDescriptor, SnapshotsContainerDescriptor, ThreadDumpDescriptor, UnknownHostDescriptor

    public interface Positionable
    Common interface for entities that can specify their position within other entities.
    Author:
    Jiri Sedlacek

    • Field Detail

      • POSITION_AT_THE_END

        static final int POSITION_AT_THE_END
        Entity will be placed before first entity with POSITION_LAST position or at the current last position if there's no entity with POSITION_LAST position.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • POSITION_LAST

        static final int POSITION_LAST
        Entity will be placed at the current last position.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • COMPARATOR

        static final Comparator COMPARATOR
        Comparator based on getPreferredPosition() value. COMPARATOR.compare(Positionable p1, Positionable p2) returns 0 only if p1.getPreferredPosition() == p2.getPreferredPosition, not to be used as a comparator for TreeSet or TreeMap.

      • STRONG_COMPARATOR

        static final Comparator STRONG_COMPARATOR
        Comparator based on getPreferredPosition() value. COMPARATOR.compare(Positionable p1, Positionable p2) returns 0 only if p1.equals(p2), safe to be used as a comparator for TreeSet or TreeMap.
        Since:
        VisualVM 1.3
